    <note type="biography">
        <p>Statesman. Styled Viscount Castlereagh from 1796. Chief secretary of Ireland, 1798–1801. President, (East India) Board of Control, 1802–5. Secretary of state for the War and Colonial Department, 1805; secretary of state for war, 1807–9. Foreign secretary, 1812–22. Succeeded as 2d marquess of Londonderry in 1821.</p></note>
